---
/**
 * rest-api/0007 · Figure 6 — the cache key and the Vary trap: the default key is
 * the URL; Vary adds request headers to it; the auth pitfall is a shared cache
 * serving one user's authed response to another.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the kebab-case-SVG reason. No arrowhead markers, so no
 * local <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 170"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Cache key defaults to the URL; the Vary header adds request headers to the key so different representations get separate entries; getting it wrong leaks the wrong user's data from a shared cache"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE CACHE KEY — AND WHY VARY GUARDS IT</text
            >
            <rect x="20" y="34" width="270" height="120" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="155"
                y="54"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">DEFAULT KEY = URL</text
            >
            <text x="155" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >one entry per /resource</text
            >
            <text x="155" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700"
                >+ Vary: Accept</text
            >
            <text x="155" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >JSON entry ≠ XML entry</text
            >
            <text x="155" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700"
                >+ Vary: Accept-Encoding</text
            >
            <text x="155" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >gzip entry ≠ brotli entry</text
            >
            <rect x="350" y="34" width="270" height="120" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="485"
                y="54"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">THE AUTH PITFALL</text
            >
            <text x="485" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >shared cache + authed response</text
            >
            <text x="485" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >→ user A's data served to user B 💥</text
            >
            <text
                x="485"
                y="116"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Fix: private · no-store</text
            >
            <text
                x="485"
                y="132"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">or Vary: Authorization</text
            >
            <text x="485" y="148" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >default authed responses to private,no-store</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        By default a cache keys on the URL. <code>Vary</code> adds request headers to that key. Get it
        wrong and the cache serves the wrong representation — or worse, the wrong user's data.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
